### Test 4: Create user with valid data (should work)
POST http://localhost:5098/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "Test",
    "lastName": "User",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "phoneNumber": "555-1234"
}

###

### Test 5: Create user with missing required fields (should fail validation)
POST http://localhost:5098/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "",
    "lastName": "",
    "email": "invalid-email"
}

###

### Test 6: Create user with invalid email (should fail validation)
POST http://localhost:5098/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "email": "not-an-email",
    "phoneNumber": "555-1234"
}

###

### Test 7: Create user with null/empty body (should crash or fail)
POST http://localhost:5098/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{}

